1 Brad Pitt’s 105-year-old tenant Actor, producer and … landlord? Pitt graciously hosted his elderly neighbor rent-free (until the day he died) on his 1.9-acre estate in L.A., according to its former owner, horror icon Elvira (aka Cassandra Peterson). 2 Jack Black and Lizzo on The Mandalorian This is the way … to surprise Star Wars fans. The famous favorites turned up in an episode of the Disney+ series as the posh rulers of a planet called Plazir-15. 3 Breakfast ramen Noodling around with the most important meal of the day, Nissin is releasing a limited-edition cup with sausage and egg bits and a pancake and maple-syrup-flavored sauce. 4 A Moana remake What can he say except “You’re welcome”? A ROYAL BLUE EASTER Windsor, England, April 9 Prince William and Princess Kate stepped out for the Easter Sunday service at St. George’s Chapel in Windsor Castle with their children Prince George, 9, and Princess Charlotte, 7, as well as Prince Louis, 4, who tagged along for the first time. After church the children, who matched their parents in shades of blue, greeted Dean of Windsor David Conner. MALTI’S MILESTONE Priyanka Chopra Jonas celebrated her 14-month-old daughter Malti’s first trip to India with a visit to the Siddhivinayak Temple in Mumbai, which she documented on Instagram April 6. A STRONG FORCE London, April 7 Daisy Ridley took the stage at the 2023 Star Wars Celebration event, where it was announced she will reprise her role as Rey in a new Star Wars film. When Taylor Swift kicked off her long-awaited Eras tour in Glendale, Ariz., on March 17, the pop star was in high spirits throughout the three-hour set, cracking jokes along the way for some 69,000 fans. But behind the scenes she was facing personal upheaval: the unraveling of her six-year relationship with actor Joe Alwyn. “They’ve had rough patches before and always worked things out, so friends thought they would take some time apart but eventually come back together,” says a source, who adds that Swift initiated the breakup in March. “Ultimately they weren’t the right fit for one another.” Throughout their years together, Swift, 33, and Alwyn, 32, kept their romance out of the public eye. In their early days as a couple, the singer hid from the public while recording…

Hilary Swank & Philip Schneider “It wasn’t easy. But boy (and girl!) was it worth it,” the two-time Oscar winner, 48, wrote on Instagram April 9, announcing the arrival of her twins with her entrepreneur husband, 50. The baby boy and girl are the first children for Swank and Schneider, who wed in 2018. “This is something that I’ve been wanting for a long time,” she said in October. Keshia Knight Pulliam & Brad James On April 9 the Cosby Show alum revealed that she and her actor husband, 41, welcomed their first child together the same week she turned 44. “With this little one we are complete,” Knight Pulliam—who is also mom to daughter Ella, 6, from a previous relationship—captioned a family photo.…

HAPPY ANNIVERSARY Beyoncé & Jay-Z The “Break My Soul” singer, 41, and the hip-hop mogul, 53, celebrated 15 years of marriage on April 4. “You have to find a person you can make it through the tough times with,” she previously said of their marriage. IT’S OVER Elle Fanning & Max Minghella In a new interview with Harper’s Bazaar U.K., the Great actress, 25, confirmed that she and the Handmaid’s Tale actor, 37, recently split. They began dating after they met while filming the 2018 musical-drama Teen Spirit. ENGAGED Lukas Gage & Chris Appleton The White Lotus actor Gage (left), 27, and celebrity hairstylist Appleton, 39, are engaged, sources confirm. “They seem like the real deal,” an insider says of the pair, who first sparked romance buzz in February.
